org.team5940.robot_core.modules

Class ModuleHashTable<T extends Module>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Dictionary<K,V>
      • java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,T>
        • org.team5940.robot_core.modules.ModuleHashTable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the modules you want to store.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,T>

    public class ModuleHashTable<T extends Module>
extends java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,T>
    Extension of Hashtable that forces the keys to be their names and provides useful methods. Useful for storing multiple Module s.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getDirectSubModulesAssignableTo

        public <M extends Module> ModuleHashTable<M> getDirectSubModulesAssignableTo(java.lang.Class<M> parent)
                                                                      throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Gets all of the Modules contained in this ModuleList where parent.isAssignableFrom(sub.getClass()) returns true.
        Parameters:
        parent - The class that you want Modules to be assignable from.
        Returns:
        A ModuleList containing direct submodules that are assignable from parent.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if parent is null.

      • getAllSubModulesAssignableTo

        public <M extends Module> ModuleHashTable<M> getAllSubModulesAssignableTo(java.lang.Class<M> parent)
                                                                   throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Gets all of the Modules contained in this ModuleList, including submodules of Modules, where where parent.isAssignableFrom(sub.getClass()) returns true.
        Parameters:
        parent - The class that you want Modules to be assignable from.
        Returns:
        A ModuleList containing all submodules that are assignable from parent.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If parent is null.

      • getAllSubModules

        public ModuleHashTable<Module> getAllSubModules()
        Gets ALL modules stored in this hash table. No order is guaranteed.
        Returns:
        A ModuleHashTable with the same type as this with the modules and all submodules contained in this.
